content_vision: My life is busy. Your is too. Sometimes everyone needs to relax. This is a happy and fast song about being relaxed.
structure_suggestion_description: Fast but happy song about being relaxed.
text:
Intro:
i ain't worried 'bout no love, just wanna hop in my honda,
school lessons got me stressing, but i know one day soon, i'll be a chosen one.

Verse 1:
i got my flossy crew, we dropping g's,
never met a guy like me, they call me g- frees.
clouds cleared, the sun came out to shine,
we stick together, we can beat them, for all time.
ain't nothing wrong with that, just speaking my mind,
you man love hezi, but you're so far behind.
preacher man spreadin' the gospel,
keep the beats comin', never gonna stop flowin'.

Pre-Chorus 1:
all right, stop, if you get where i'm coming from,
but if you don't, then you'll never see the outcome.

Chorus 1:
i wanna be like those who got it all,
but it makes me wonder why i'm still here, trying to crawl.
you know you can't pretend, can't keep up the fa√ßade,
only money in the way, but it's not the real god.

Verse 2:
you better know that i'm comin' with my squad,
and when we blast that sniper music, you'll feel awed.
bump bump bump, just like 50 cent,
are you waiting for someone
or are you overdosing on this hype overload?
the sun finally came out,
you spent ten thousand on that birkin bag,
you got a lotta cash, but none of it can last.

Pre-Chorus 2:
all that we are is what we need,
but i get by on faith and a little greed.

Chorus 2:
nobody was really sure where to go,
needed a vision correction, knew that it was time to grow.
my brain release, got racks on my plate,
messy life, but i ain't never gon' be clean.

Bridge:
you're searching for excuses, but there's no need,
this fake girl be lyin' with her fake tan and deeds.
no luxury, just a quick fuck in the honda,
and now we're living bland and plain, but back then they said my pussy tasted like candy, took them all by surprise.

Outro:
life's a mess, can't seem to find order,
we just tryna stack this cash and avoid the chatter,

Instrumental:
rollin' in the dough, bitch i'm cashed out,
and even when he's gone, his memory never leaves me with doubt.
